Specimen Type(s): Surgical pathology slides prepared from FFPE tissue
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for Proscia Concentriq Dx software for digital image viewing and management of FFPE surgical pathology slides
Indications for Use Summary: Software-only device for in vitro diagnostic use, aiding pathologists in viewing, interpretation, and management of digital images of scanned FFPE surgical pathology slides for primary diagnosis, not intended for frozen sections, cytology, or non-FFPE hematopathology specimens, for use with Hamamatsu NanoZoomer S360MD Slide scanner and JVC JD-C240BN01A monitor.
